  "text": "Formaldehyde gas sensors and biosensors often furthermore lack the required selectivity [CITATION_1] . [CITATION_2] Traditional methods to detect formaldehyde are based on either the collection of formaldehyde by active or passive sampling in cartridges impregnated with 2,4-dinitrophenylhydrazine [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] 25] or are aqueous based [CITATION_5] followed by the analysis of the formed hydrazones by HPLC. These methods however require post sample preparation steps and the acceptor solution can be subject to evaporation in high flow-rate air samples.",
