      "citation_id": "[CITATION_3]",
      "span_text": "Traditional methods to detect formaldehyde are based on either the collection of formaldehyde by active or passive sampling in cartridges impregnated with 2,4-dinitrophenylhydrazine   25] or are aqueous based  followed by the analysis of the formed hydrazones by HPLC. These methods however require post sample preparation steps and the acceptor solution can be subject to evaporation in high flow-rate air samples."
